Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Edegel, Southern Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-16T20:27:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/peru-stocks-buenaventura-edegel-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index was little changed at 20,984.13. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.7 percent to 2,912.02.  Miners declined amid investor concern that  Japan ’s crisis
will curb short-term demand for metals, Luis Felipe Arizmendi,
president of Lima-based brokerage GPI Valores, said in an
interview.    Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, fell 2.5 percent to $39.70. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura
SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-metals miner, slid
1.7 percent to $42.25. Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAC1 PE), a
unit of Gold Fields Ltd., dropped for a third session, losing
1.3 percent to 3.11 soles. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE),
Peru’s biggest silver producer, dropped 1.3 percent to 3.70
soles.  Construction and energy stocks rose after the government
said home-building and electricity helped drive 10 percent
economic growth in January.    Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm, gained 2.7 percent to 6.40 soles. Edegel SA
(EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s Endesa SA, rose 2.6
percent to 1.95 soles after Peru’s electricity output rose 9
percent in February, according to the Energy Ministry.  Cementos
Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest cement maker,
climbed 0.8 percent to 38.25 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  